      "source": "<a href=\"http://twitter.com/download/iphone\" rel=\"nofollow\">Twitter for iPhone</a>",
      "text": "Please join me in praying for the family of Coast Guard Petty Officer 2nd Class Tyler Jaggers.\n\nTyler Jaggers, an aviation survival technician assigned to Air Station Astoria, Oregon, passed away yesterday, as a result of critical injuries sustained during a February 27 medical evacuation mission which was offshore from Cape Flattery, Washington.\n \nPrior to Tyler Jaggers passing, surrounded by his parents, sister, fiance, friends, and @USCG temamates, Jaggers was meritoriously advanced to Petty Officer Second Class and awarded the Distinguished Flying Cross—one of the highest military awards for heroism during aerial flight. \n\nWe are grateful for his faithful service.",
      "text_resolved": "Please join me in praying for the family of Coast Guard Petty Officer 2nd Class Tyler Jaggers.\n\nTyler Jaggers, an aviation survival technician assigned to Air Station Astoria, Oregon, passed away yesterday, as a result of critical injuries sustained during a February 27 medical evacuation mission which was offshore from Cape Flattery, Washington.\n \nPrior to Tyler Jaggers passing, surrounded by his parents, sister, fiance, friends, and @USCG temamates, Jaggers was meritoriously advanced to Petty Officer Second Class and awarded the Distinguished Flying Cross—one of the highest military awards for heroism during aerial flight. \n\nWe are grateful for his faithful service.",
